  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_5' aria-label=\" Subha Prasad Nandi Majumdar versus The State of West Bengal Service & Ors pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('5','2025','2025_7_1808_1822','2025INSC910'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SUBHA PRASAD NANDI MAJUMDAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF WEST BENGAL SERVICE & ORS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 1808</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 910</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008182025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANOJ MISRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the correctness of the order passed by the Division Bench of the High Court upholding the University and State&rsquo;s stance that government Notification dated 24.02.2021 extending the retirement age from 60 to 65 years appellant due to non-satisfaction of the 10-year continuous teaching condition in a university situated in West Bengal. Headnotes&dagger; Service law &ndash; Retirement &ndash; Extension of retirement age from 60 to 65 years &ndash; Appellant served as a teaching staff member for 16 years at a<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 30-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 9913/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('5','2025','2025_7_1808_1822','2025INSC910','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split